Sentencas: The ruthenium Pyrochlores, A(2)Ru(2)O(7-delta) (A = Pb Bi), and ruthenium perovskites, (ARuO(3) (A = Ca, Sr) were characterized as new electrode materials fur solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: New cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells - Ruthenium pyrochlores and perovskites

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity, cathodic polarization, thermal expansion, and reactivity with yttria-stabilized zirconia were examined.
Titulo: New cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells - Ruthenium pyrochlores and perovskites

Sentencas: The pyrochlores showed low cathodic overpotential even at 800 degrees C, metallic behavior with high electrical conductivity, and no reaction with yttria-stabilized zirconia at 900 degrees C.
Titulo: New cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells - Ruthenium pyrochlores and perovskites

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient of the bismuth pyrochlore was comparable to yttria-stabilized (8 mol % Y2O3 content) zirconia.
Titulo: New cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells - Ruthenium pyrochlores and perovskites

Sentencas: The pyrochlores are very attractive for application as cathode materials in a solid oxide fuel cell with low operating temperature.
Titulo: New cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells - Ruthenium pyrochlores and perovskites
